<section class="about-taniti">
    <p>Taniti is a small, tropical island in the Pacific. The island's terrain includes sandy beaches, rocky beaches, lush rainforests, and a small, active volcano. The population is about 20,000 indigenous residents.</p>
    <p>Until a recent tourism boom, Taniti's economy was primarily based on fishing and agriculture. Today, Taniti is a growing tourist destination known for its natural beauty, outdoor adventures, and welcoming atmosphere.</p>
